			  			<HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  			I don't like bringing up a bug like this, but I guess we need to post the good ones with the bad ones.<br />
<br />
I have been watching my commander abilities for several sets now and have found the following.  When I played Bosalians last set, the highest starting detection at first level was 8.  I'm guessing that this is from a base of 5 plus 3 for Mental Giant (my observations have led me to believe that Mental Giant gives an immediate bonus of +3 with the other +7 distributed as you go up in level - but I digress).  I had several eights at level one last set with the Bosalians and of course all of them were Mental Giants.  This set I'm playing my usual race again, Xeloss, and have recently seen a detection of 7 at level one and my Genius is still at 1 so I'm not getting a lot of the really good commanders yet.  Of course, my commander also had Mental Giant, but the Xeloss race supposedly has -2 to detection.  So if my observations are correct, that would mean that my commander had a detection score of 6 with +3 for Mental Giant and -2 for Race.<br />
<br />
I'm only asking that someone check out the code and verify that the racial modifiers are actually being applied.						<P align=right> </P>
