			  	Splinter;<br />
<br />
If you run a statistical analysis on your commanders, you will find that the racial modifiers are not part of the numbers on the screen.  Don't get fooled by the modifiers from commander abilities when making your calculations.<br />
<br />
As for Mental Giant, it appears (looking at the means, modes, medians, max, and min values - I didn't need to bother with standard deviations and such to determine how the actual values are distributed - I'm only a player so mathematics is all I have to rely on because I don't have the code) that you get +3 to detection at level 1 and it goes up from there so that at level 20 you have a total of +10 that can be attributed to Mental Giant.<br />
<br />
Embryodead mentioned that the numbers would change next set, more of the bonuses would be available up front than later in the game.  Personally, I would like to see half of the total bonuses up front and the rest distributed linearly as you go up in level.  But that is just my personal preference, it is not for me to decide.			   <P align=right></P>
